      "id": 7,
      "prompt": "I have an existing FastAPI app that produces JSON messages to Kafka without Schema Registry. Here's my current producer code:\n\n```python\n# app/kafka_producer.py\nfrom confluent_kafka import Producer\nimport json\nimport os\n\nproducer = Producer({'bootstrap.servers': os.environ['BOOTSTRAP_SERVER']})\n\ndef send_event(topic: str, event: dict):\n    producer.produce(topic, value=json.dumps(event).encode('utf-8'))\n    producer.poll(0)\n```\n\nI want to add Schema Registry integration. I'm on Confluent Cloud. My events look like: {\"user_id\": \"abc\", \"action\": \"page_view\", \"url\": \"/home\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-13T10:00:00Z\"}",
      "expected_output": "The skill should NOT scaffold a brand new project. It should: (1) generate a JSON Schema from the existing message structure, (2) generate common.py and schemas/value.schema.json, (3) modify the existing producer code to use JSONSerializer with Schema Registry instead of raw json.dumps, (4) set auto.register.schemas=false. The modified producer should preserve the existing function signature as much as possible.",
      "files": [
        {
          "path": "app/kafka_producer.py",
          "content": "from confluent_kafka import Producer\nimport json\nimport os\n\nproducer = Producer({'bootstrap.servers': os.environ['BOOTSTRAP_SERVER']})\n\ndef send_event(topic: str, event: dict):\n    producer.produce(topic, value=json.dumps(event).encode('utf-8'))\n    producer.poll(0)\n"
        }
      ],
